The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	State sports minister Subhas Chakraborty on Monday will formally inaugurate the ticket sales at the Netaji Indoor Stadium for the exhibition match between CMs XI and External Affairs Ministers XI. Diego Maradona will be present during the match on Saturday.           
	 Leander Paes has been nominated vice-president of the Bengal Tennis Association (BTA) at the 67th annual general meeting at the BTA Complex on Saturday.       
	THE COMMITTEE: President: Sushil Mehrotra; Vice-presidents: Chuni Goswami, Akhtar Ali, Leander Paes, A.K Sinha, P. Roy Chowdhury, C.V Muralidhar, Hermanprit Singh; Secretary: Hironmoy Chatterjee; Treasurer: Mihir Mitra                
	 Kamran Ali beat Jaffer Javed in the boys under 12 final of the 44th Floodlit Tennis tournament at the Saturday Club on Sunday. In the ladies section, Ragini Vimal, Mika Mohuri, Andrea Das won their respective matches.                                                                                                                                                                     
